title: Who is contributing to Ron Paul, USA, 1st Quarter 2007
name: Who is contributing to Ron Paul, USA, 1st Quarter 2007
description: Ron Paul is one of the seven or eight Republican candidates waging a campaign for GOP's nomination. He represents 14th congressional districts from Texas http://www.house.gov/paul/ . Knowing how public thinks of the U.S. Congress its surprising that Ron Paul is one of the most sought after candidates online and on college campuses. Politically he is more libertarian than a conservative, advocating 10% flat tax and immediate pullout from Iraq. He is going against the grain in the GOP and has very few supporters  compared to the top tier candidates. His appeal to younger generation is unique politicians of all stripes. Inspite of his age (almost 73), he has become something of a cult figure among the younger generation. He may be old however his motto (paraphrasing), Ideas related to freedom are always young" resonates among all ages. The data for the map is based on publicly disclosed contributions from Federal Election Commission's website.   Important Notice from FEC: Reports and statements filed by political committees may be inspected and copied by anyone. The names and addresses of individual contributors,  however,  may not be sold or used for any commercial purpose or to solicit any type of contribution or donation,  such as political or charitable contributions. 2 U.S.C.
